10/05/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President-elect Branko Crvenkovski's inauguration ceremony will likely be held on Wednesday (12 May), according to local media reports. Crvenkovski won nearly 53 per cent of the votes in last month's early elections, defeating main opposition party VMRO-DPMNE candidate Sasko Kedev. The State Electoral Commission certified the victory on Saturday.
In other news, Macedonia and Kosovo have agreed to complete the demarcation of the Kosovo border by 2005 at the latest. The consensus was reached Friday during a meeting between Macedonian Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski and Kosovo Prime Minister Bajram Rexhepi. (Utrinski Vesnik, Makfax - 10/05/04)
